<p>Let me mention some things not to do. The number one thing not to do is other things. If you find yourself saying a sentence that ends with â€œbut weâ€™re going to keep working on the startup,â€ you are in big trouble. Bobâ€™s going to grad school, but weâ€™re going to keep working on the startup. Weâ€™re moving back to Minnesota, but weâ€™re going to keep working on the startup. Weâ€™re taking on some consulting projects, but weâ€™re going to keep working on the startup. You may as well just translate these to â€œweâ€™re giving up on the startup, but weâ€™re not willing to admit that to ourselves,â€ because thatâ€™s what it means most of the time. A startup is so hard that working on it canâ€™t be preceded by â€œbut.â€</p>

