<p>In particular, donâ€™t go to graduate school, and donâ€™t start other projects. Distraction is fatal to startups. Going to (or back to) school is a huge predictor of death because in addition to the distraction it gives you something to say youâ€™re doing. If youâ€™re only doing a startup, then if the startup fails, you fail. If youâ€™re in grad school and your startup fails, you can say later â€œOh yeah, we had this startup on the side when I was in grad school, but it didnâ€™t go anywhere.â€</p>

